This study examines the effect of a training program on long-term-care (LTC) 
surveyors' knowledge of factors affecting oral health and their behavior in 
citing oral health deficiencies of LTC residents. Twenty surveyors were 
recruited for the experimental group, along with a non-equivalent comparison 
group of 31 surveyors. The experimental group participated in a three-hour 
interactive, case-based training program. The experimental group had a 
